<item>
            <title>[MJAVADOC-762] createTestRepo in JavaDocReportTest shares state</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-762</link>
                <project id="12317529" key="MJAVADOC">Maven Javadoc Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This test doesn&apos;t create a new repo for every test. Therefore state is shared between test methods.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Worse yet, state is shared between one run of the test suite and the next unless there&apos;s an intervening mvn clean.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This caused me some very annoying debugging for a problem that I had already fixed but the test suite kept failing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
